This paper discusses the use of deep learning techniques to model complex real-world problems, which is a common theme in the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper specifically focuses on improving the generalizability of deep models by incorporating information on auxiliary explanatory data variables, which is relevant to computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common technique in the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
